Data mining is where businesses take a vast amount of data and analyze it to locate trends. Many businesses use this method to search through their customer base and locate what section of their customers is their target market. This goes off the rule that 20% of your customers generate 80% of your profits, so once the business can locat that 20% of customers they can begin to better cater to their needs and increase their profitability further.
To mine data we take a vast table of data and ask it a query. From that query we can begin to locate different trends that the data follows. An example of this could be a company looking for the age of their target market. So in a data table, they ask the query of how many of the customers are in each age group. The query would then come back and show how many of the customers are in each age group, and from there the company can identify which group is the largest. They may even use the same method we did in class, Data Clustering.
